<p>She recently opened up to Insider about co-parenting with Jay, 37: 'I don't have any advice because I think every situation is different. </p>

<p>'But I think that Jay and I are navigating through it in the best way possible and we're figuring it out. Some days are good and some days are bad, but we're making the most of the situation and putting our kids first.'</p>

<p>Kristin and the retired NFL quarterback tied the knot in June of 2013, and they share sons Camden Jack, eight, Jaxon Wyatt, six, and daughter Saylor James, four.</p>

<p>She added that their kids are their first priority: 'They're the only things I care about right now. And so I'm removing any of my emotions or feelings and just thinking about them and putting them first.'</p>

